\mathbb{Z}^+
P(X \in (k-1,k]) = P(X>k-1) - P(X>k) = \dfrac1{2^{k-1}} - \dfrac1{2^k} = \dfrac1{2^k}
P(X \in (k-1,k]) = P(X = k) = \dfrac1{2^k}
